\par }\pard\plain \s17\sb120\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f5\fs20 {\tab All passwords in the }{\i Kerberos}{ database are encrypted in the master database key Therefore, the information passed 
from master to slave over the network is not useful to an eavesdropper. However, it is essential that only information from the master host be accepted by the slaves, and that tampering of data be detected, thus the checksum.
