\par }\pard \widctlpar\adjustright {Since most DOS and
 Macintosh programs are executed from a local disk rather than a centralized file server, DCNS developed Version Checking to let users know when new versions of their applications have been released. Because a version server machine is integral to Version
 Checking, applications with this capability are called "VS-enabled applications."
